00:01:36.000 --> 00:01:40.000
world right now. Worth a reply. Ben reacted to something

00:01:40.000 --> 00:01:44.000
medical you told him about. He said "geez, that's so

00:01:44.000 --> 00:01:48.000
ass," "so weird to come on out of nowhere," and

00:01:48.000 --> 00:01:52.000
he feels like when he hears about it, it's connected

00:01:52.000 --> 00:01:56.000
to other meds or illnesses. Whatever health thing you mentioned,

00:01:56.000 --> 00:02:00.000
he's empathizing. Worth following up there too. Your five-seven-three friend

00:02:00.000 --> 00:02:04.000
texted about going to forty-four Canteen on Friday if you're

00:02:04.000 --> 00:02:08.000
interested. That conflicts with Unbound — you'll be at Mom

00:02:08.000 --> 00:02:12.000
and Dad's Friday night. Alex sent a gif in the

00:02:12.000 --> 00:02:16.000
group chat. Quiet otherwise. Dustin still quiet. Calendar. Unbound Book

00:02:16.000 --> 00:02:20.000
Festival is day one today, April sixteenth through nineteenth in

00:02:20.000 --> 00:02:24.000
Columbia. Keynote is Terry Tempest Williams. Check the Thursday evening

00:02:24.000 --> 00:02:28.000
schedule for anything worth catching. You're staying at Mom and

00:02:28.000 --> 00:02:32.000
Dad's Friday night and doing panels Saturday. Project Arete, day

00:02:32.000 --> 00:02:36.000
four of thirty. Production over consumption. And this is the

00:02:36.000 --> 00:02:40.000
final day of the arXiv trial — day seven of

00:02:40.000 --> 00:02:44.000
seven. Decision due tomorrow. Looking ahead: Molly's Miles ten-K is

00:02:44.000 --> 00:02:48.000
nine days out, April twenty-fifth. Capital City Race is twenty-three

00:02:48.000 --> 00:02:52.000
days. W-W-D-C is fifty-three days. Now the news. The Iran

00:02:52.000 --> 00:02:56.000
